@Renesanse Hi, I played with both flutter versions, the worst situation I (or my boss) saw, was on his iPhone Xr on build with Metal support, on OpenGL it's a little better but only a little. When I started using cached shaders then on e.g. iPhone 6s (the slowest device I have) app works well and on iPhone 7, iPhone 12 Max Pro there are lags. After few reinstals (without changes in code!) app looks ok on random devices, or on all - strange and funny.

@stx I agree with your steps to improve iOS performance, but they're not fixing lags, only reducing them.

I decided to investigate Flutter as a replacement for native app development for some projects in my company but after around 3 months I have Android version of app, QA and customers will not accept that performance on iOS. It's not big problem because as I said it was investigation but now, I'm not sure if I should propose Flutter as stable framework for some serious development.

When some guy said that Flutter documentation should inform potential new devs about that problem AT THE BEGINNING where they mention about NATIVE performance - I totally agree with him.

@Hixie Thanks for the explanation. Looking at the priority rules, it sounds like this would be a P1 issue if it was blocking someone with representation ("top-tier customer"), but if it's blocking someone without representation (small project or large project that does not have a formal relationship with Google) it's P3.

I would suggest that there should be situations where P3 can be bumped to P2 or P1 that doesn't hinge solely on their "relationship status" with Google, as a sum effect of a blocker, especially one that appears to be reputation threatening, would arguably exceed the negative impact of blocking one top-tier customer.

As a slightly humorous indicator of the seriousness of this issue, it has been reported that this is spawning conspiracy theory videos saying Apple has hamstrung Flutter intentionally by forcing migration to Metal. Maybe P1 could also be for issues that are breeding conspiracy theories. 😅
